data.chText: 随机的，随意的（非事先决定或不规则）
data.enText: done, chosen, etc. without sb deciding in advance what is going to happen, or without any regular pattern
the random killing of innocent people
a random sample/selection (= in which each thing has an equal chance of being chosen)

data.chText: 信息是按随机顺序处理的。
data.enText: The information is processed in a random order.

data.chText: 中奖号码是由电脑随机选取的。
data.enText: The winning numbers are randomly selected by computer.

data.chText: 我的手机好像随时自动关机。
data.enText: My phone seems to switch itself off randomly.

data.chText: 这就为形势增加了一种不确定因素。
data.enText: It introduced an element of randomness into the situation.
without deciding in advance what is going to happen, or without any regular pattern

data.chText: 她随意翻到一页就看了起来。
data.enText: She opened the book at random (= not at any particular page) and started reading.

data.chText: 恐怖分子胡乱地向人群开枪。
data.enText: The terrorists fired into the crowd at random.

data.chText: 名字是从名单中随便点的。
data.enText: Names were chosen at random from a list.

simple_means.memory_skill: ran 跑 + dom 情况，身份，状态，性质 → 随便跑 → 任意

means: 随机的，随意的(非事先决定或不规则)

ex.chText: 在店内随机选择了一些女性进行了调查。
ex.enText: The survey was conducted based on a random selection of women who were in the shop.

synonyms.bx: 指无计划或目的地选择或发生的。

ex.chText: 事实上，他们的相遇并不是偶然的。
ex.enText: In fact, their meeting was not accidental.

ex.chText: 由于设计方案意外泄漏，该公司失去了优势。
ex.enText: The company lost its advantages due to an accidental leak of its designs.

synonyms.bx: 指计划外或无意间发生的。

ex.chText: 她在一次偶然的谈话中第一次听到他的名字。
ex.enText: She first heard of his name in a casual conversation.

ex.chText: 教授对他的论文随口点评了几句。
ex.enText: The professor made some casual remarks about his paper.

synonyms.bx: 指随意、并无计划的，只作定语。

data.enText: without deciding in advance what is going to happen, or without any regular pattern

data.chText: 她随意翻到一页就看了起来。
data.enText: She opened the book at random (= not at any particular page) and started reading.

data.chText: 恐怖分子胡乱地向人群开枪。
data.enText: The terrorists fired into the crowd at random.

data.enText: Names were chosen at random from a list.

tr: lacking any definite plan or order or purpose
governed by or depending on chance

value.def: A random sample or method is one in which all the people or things involved have an equal chance of being chosen.

example.ex: The survey used a random sample of two thousand people across England and Wales...
example.tran: 该调查在英格兰和威尔士随机抽样了2,000人。

example.ex: The competitors will be subject to random drug testing.
example.tran: 参赛者将要接受随机药检。

example.ex: ...interviews with a randomly selected sample of thirty girls aged between 13 and 18.
example.tran: 在13到18岁女孩中随机抽取30位进行访谈

value.def: If you describe events as random, you mean that they do not seem to follow a definite plan or pattern.

example.tran: 加诸无辜受害者的无端暴行

example.ex: Children's words and actions are often fairly random.
example.tran: 小孩子的言行常常是随性而为。

example.ex: ...drinks and magazines left scattered randomly around.
example.tran: 到处都是随手乱丢的饮料和杂志

example.ex: Isn't this a demand to control the randomness of life?
example.tran: 这难道不是要求对生命的无常加以控制吗？

value.def: If you choose people or things at random, you do not use any particular method, so they all have an equal chance of being chosen.

example.ex: We received several answers, and we picked one at random.
example.tran: 我们收到了一些答复，并从中随机挑选了一个。

value.def: If something happens at random, it happens without a definite plan or pattern.

example.ex: Three black people were killed by shots fired at random from a minibus.
example.tran: 3名黑人被从一辆面包车里胡乱射出的子弹打死了。
